            <h1>How to Use</h1>
            <p>Choose an apparatus from the bar at the top of the screen - <a href="/bars">Bars</a>, <a href="/beam">Beam</a>, or <a href="/floor">Floor</a>. From there, add individual skills to your routine by clicking the Add Skill button. Your options will appear to the right. As you add skills, the D-Score of the routine will be updated and displayed at the bottom left.</p>
            <p>To connect one skill to another, click on the &#xFF0B icon next to the skill you want to connect. To delete a skill from a connection, click on the &#x232B icon. Finally, to delete an entire row of connected skills, click on the &#x24CD icon.</p>
            <p>Sometimes, you will not be able to add, connect, or delete skills. This is because doing so would result in a routine that is impossible to perform. For example, on bars, you often cannot remove transitions between the bars as this would result in the gymnast being on one bar one second and the other bar the next. As another example, on beam, you cannot add any additional skills once the dismount has been performed. The add and delete buttons will be disabled in such cases.</p>
