        <h1>How Scores Are Calculated</h1>
        <p>Each skill is assigned a Difficulty Value, ranging from A (0.1 points) to J (1 point).Â The seven skills with the highest Difficulty Values, plus the dismount, are added together to form the basis of the Difficulty Score (D-Score). On beam and floor, the skills that count toward the D-Score must be well-split between acro and dance. The gymnast is also awarded Connection Value (CV) for certain connections. Finally, each apparatus has a group of four Composition Requirements (CR) that are each worth 0.5 points. To maximize her score, a gymnast should fulfill all four Composition Requirements.</p>
        
